Class StringGeneratorBuilder

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public abstract class StringGeneratorBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.jnape.palatable.lambda.adt.coproduct.CoProduct2<dev.marksman.kraftwerk.StringGeneratorBuilder.Plain,dev.marksman.kraftwerk.StringGeneratorBuilder.Maybes,StringGeneratorBuilder>
    A builder that facilitates creating Generators for complex Strings.

    After instantiating a StringGeneratorBuilder, you can call the various add methods to specify "segments" of the final output, and then call build() to create the Generator. When the Generator is invoked, all segments will be joined together in the order they were specified.

    A StringGeneratorBuilder is immutable and can be used to construct multiple Generators. All methods that alter a StringGeneratorBuilder return a new StringGeneratorBuilder; the old one will still exist unchanged. A StringGeneratorBuilder will always remain valid and reusable, even if build has already been called.

      • withSeparator

        public abstract StringGeneratorBuilder withSeparator(Generator<java.lang.String> newSeparator)
        Creates a new StringGeneratorBuilder that is the same as this one, with the separator to be generated by the provided Generator. This replaces any previous value for the separator.

        The separator will be placed between segments in the final output. The Generator for the separator will be invoked every time a separator is called for in the output, not just once per output.

        Parameters:
        newSeparator - the Generator for separators
        Returns:
        a StringGeneratorBuilder

      • build

        public abstract Generator<java.lang.String> build()
        Creates a Generator from this StringGeneratorBuilder. The resulting Generator will, each time it is invoked, generate all segments that were specified and concatenate them (optionally separated by the separator and surrounded by the delimiters).

        This StringGeneratorBuilder will remain valid after calling build, and can continue to be built upon.

        Returns:
        a Generator<String>
